<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-06-16T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-06-16T16:00:00-05:00" n="1117" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1117">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 867.4016/287a</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Turkey</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Philip</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-06-16T16:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 16, 1916, 4 p. m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>2758. Reports have reached the Department that situation of Armenian
                            exiles in Mesopotamia is daily becoming worse—that great numbers are
                            dying of hunger and sickness, and children are sold openly in markets.
                            If true, again urge Turkish Government in name of humanity to alleviate
                            condition remnants of this race.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>